The paper deals with hardware security and specifically focuses on detecting Hardware Trojans (HT) in Register Transfer Level (RTL) designs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a new approach to security analysis of RTL designs, which involves investigating design properties, and this could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper deals with the design of hardware circuits, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also involves analyzing the interactions between nets in a design, which could fall under cs.DC (Digital Circuits) or cs.ET (Emerging Technologies).
